{
  "doc_id": "11750",
  "text": "The LSD algorithm [CITATION_1] is an excellent line segment detection method based on phase grouping and does not require parameter tuning. In [CITATION_2] , a line segment is defined as an image region whose points share roughly the same gradient orientation. The procedure of the LSD algorithm is given as follows: first, pixels that share the same gradient orientation up to a given tolerance are grouped as a connected region, i.e., the line support region. Then, the line segment that best approximates each line-support region is extracted according to rectangular approximation rules. Finally, each line segment is validated or not based on a contrario model.",
